title: Audi e-tron GT
description: The Audi e-tron GT is available in two variants including etron GT and Rs etron GT. Market introduction: The Audi etron GT was launched in India on 22 September, 2021, with prices starting at Rs 1.80 crore (ex-showroom).

title: Audi RS e-tron GT
description: Two powerful electric motors provide dynamic driving performance and confident electric all-wheel drive. With its net energy content of 84 kWh, the high-voltage battery enables ranges of up to 488 km (303.2 mi) and can be recharged extremely quickly, thanks to its 800 V technology.

title: Toyota Rav4 Car
description: The Toyota RAV4 (Japanese: トヨタ・RAV4, Hepburn: Toyota Ravufō) is a compact crossover SUV (sport utility vehicle) produced by the Japanese automobile manufacturer Toyota.

title: Toyota Harrier
description: The Toyota Harrier is powerful, spacious, easy to handle, and has a premium feel to it. The Harrier is a compact mid-size crossover SUV with luxury and advanced technology. It features Nanoe™ X Technology & S-FLOW Control for your comfort and fuel efficiency.

title: Nissan X-trail
description: The Nissan X-trail is a compact crossover SUV produced by the Japanese automaker Nissan. It offers a powerful advanced 1995cc diesel engine that provides 142bhp@4000rpm maximum power and 200Nm@2000rpm maximum torque. The X-Trail exterior offers the signature Nissan V-Motion grille, rear styling plate and chrome door sills.
